This template is intended to simplify entering the references to the basic laws (Constitutions and Charters) of the [[federal subjects of Russia]] and their top-level [[subdivisions of Russia#Municipal divisions|municipal divisions]] (urban okrugs and municipal districts).

==Syntax==
<pre><nowiki>
{{RussiaBasicLawRef
|FS=
|uppermundiv=
}}
</nowiki></pre>

==Usage==

<code><nowiki>{{RussiaBasicLawRef|FS= |uppermundiv=}}</nowiki></code>

;Parameters
*''FS'', or the first unnamed parameter, is the [[ISO 3166-2:RU]] code (without the "RU" part) of the federal subject to which the item being referenced belongs. For example, [[Altai Krai]] is coded as "alt".
*''uppermundiv'', or the second unnamed parameter, is the name of the urban okrug or municipal district (without the "urban okrug" and "municipal district" designations), to which the information being cited pertains. There is no default value.

;No parameters
When called without parameters, the template returns the citation for the [[Constitution of Russia]].

==Examples==

 <nowiki>{{RussiaBasicLawRef|FS=alt}}</nowiki>

This will display as:

{{RussiaBasicLawRef|FS=alt}}

 <nowiki>{{RussiaBasicLawRef|bel|borisovsky}}</nowiki>

This will display as:

{{RussiaBasicLawRef|bel|borisovsky}}

 <nowiki>{{RussiaBasicLawRef}}</nowiki>

This will display as:

{{RussiaBasicLawRef}}

==Important notes==
The templates uses the parameters submitted to it to call an appropriate subtemplate (for example, {{tl|RussiaBasicLawRef/alt}}).  If the subtemplate does not exist, the call will fail, producing an ugly red link.  Make sure you create a proper subtemplate first if one does not yet exist.  A list of existing subtemplates is available in [[:Category:Subtemplates of Template RussiaBasicLawRef]].
